Adjacent to the DART rail and the fitness-cenetric Katy Trail, the building is conveniently located in a neighborhood brimming with diverse and thriving dining, retail and entertainment. 6060 at The Crossing actively bridges the gap between work and life.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Centrally located amongst Dallas’ most affluent neighborhood Highland Park, on the heels of the Katy Trail, and with easy access from North Central Expressway, Knox Street continues to thrive. The Knox Street District, Dallas’ most pedestrian friendly walking district, has always been a coveted location for retailers and office users alike.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Weir’s Plaza is bringing a world-class office and retail experience through an iconic building that speaks to the history of the neighborhood as well as the future.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Located at the intersection of Downtown, Deep Ellum and the Dallas Farmers Market. Adjacent to major thoroughfares, as well as the restaurants, shops and entertainment venues of the neighborhood, The Epic's convenient and creative culture provides effortless walkability to the most business-rich districts in the city.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The Epic contemporary office tower boast Class AA office space with thoughtful amenities. The 251,000 SF building, designed by global architecture firm Perkins+Will, offers a dynamic and engaging environment built with innovative offerings. Work compliments life via outdoor spaces, private terraces, multiple collaborative areas, and a 7th floor rooftop amenity deck with a fitness center and sweeping view of Downtown Dallas.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: 4040 NCX will be a short five minute walk to the next major mixed-use development in Dallas – The Central. With Phase I of construction for The Central starting in 2020, 4040 NCX employees will soon be in close proximity to an additional 110,000 SF of retail/restaurants, 750 apartment units and 450 hotel rooms.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Steps to the Arts District and the best of Downtown Dallas. 717 Harwood is on the doorstep of the largest arts district in the US, home to the Meyerson Symphony Center, Dallas Museum of Art, Nasher Sculpture Center, Winspear Opera House, and more. Klyde Warren Park is a 5.2 acre green space that provides a (literal) bridge between Downtown and Uptown Dallas. Tenants can walk one block south to catch the Dart Rail - the largest lightrial system in the US, giving them rail access to virtually anywhere in the Metroplex.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: 717 Harwood offers a tenant-focused experience in the heart of the cultural center of Dallas. And 34 floors, some of the best panoramic views in Downtown Dallas. The highly efficient floor plates range from 22,000 to 28,000 square feet and provide maximum flexibilty in space planning and the ability to accomodate small to large tenants. The building lends itself to both "creative" space with exposed ceilings, sealed concrete floors, and raw material surfaces, as well as traditional office space, which has allowed the current tenant base to create a more inviting and engaging workplace. Vacancies available from 1,000 SF to full floors, including 180,000 SF of contiguous space - the second largest in Dallas CBD.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: 2100 McKinney offers the most convenient location in Dallas. The building's tenants have access (across the street or just a few blocks away) to a variety of restaurants (for a quick snack or elegant business dinners), full-service banks, Dallas' finest hotels (The Ritz-Carlton, and The Crescent), shopping, the award winning Klyde Warren Park and several health clubs and spas.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Located where Uptown meets Downtown, 2100 McKinney is the business address for companies needing to be surrounded by the most amenities and services Dallas/For Worth has to offer. 2100 McKinney provides efficient floor plates, outstanding views, a 3:1,000 parking ratio, and immediate access to all major thoroughfares.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Renaissance Tower is a 56-story, 1,738,979 square foot Class A trophy office tower located in the heart of the Dallas Central Business District. Completed in 1974, the office tower was substantially renovated between 1986 and 1991 and emerged with a heightened image and even more illustrious profile within Downtown Dallas. Renowned for its distinctive double "X" lighting and majestic rooftop spires, Renaissance Tower is a Dallas Landmark.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Class A trophy office tower located in the heart of the Dallas Central Business District.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Fountain Place is the best located building in the Arts District. Its strategic location is unsurpassed with direct access to I-35, I-75 and I-30, and less than a mile from the Dallas North Tollway. No matter where you’re going, you’ll get there easily. The tree-lined courtyard and iconic water gardens at Fountain Place is an oasis within the city. It offers abundant amenities in every direction of the property.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Fountain Place defines the City’s skyline. It is a Dallas landmark, an instantly recognizable 58-story glass prism that defines the City’s skyline. With its crisp geometry and surrounding water gardens, it is the inspiration of legendary architects brought to life. Just as the building's shape changes at different angles, Fountain Place has evolved in order to maintain its rightful place as a remarkable location in the minds of locals and visitors alike. This year, Fountain Place has undergone an extensive renovation that carefully and thoughtfully updates all of the building interiors to be as timeless as the iconic exterior.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: An Icon of the Dallas Skyline. Now Reimagined.
